3. Range of Trust Bank Operations

What is a Trust?

A trust bank Is a bank that engages in both banking business and trust business.

Trust banks are banks under the Banking Act that are granted permission based on the Act on Engagement in Trust Business Activities by Financial Institutions to also conduct trust business.
